{%- comment -%}
  ASR Outdoor — VideoObject schema for video "watch page" articles.

  WHY: Shopify strips <script> JSON-LD from article bodies, so the VideoObject
  structured data has to be emitted by the theme. The live YouTube player itself
  goes in the article body (Claude inserts the <iframe> via the API); THIS block
  only outputs the schema Google needs to treat the page as a watch page.

  WHERE TO PASTE (one time):
    Online Store -> Themes -> Edit code -> sections/main-article.liquid
    Paste this whole block near the TOP of the file (just inside the section,
    before the article content markup). The `article` object is in scope there.

  It only fires when an article has a `custom.youtube_id` metafield, so it has
  ZERO effect on your Journal blog posts.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign yt = article.metafields.custom.youtube_id -%}
{%- if yt != blank -%}
  {%- assign vdesc = article.metafields.custom.video_description | default: article.excerpt | default: article.content | strip_html | truncate: 320 -%}
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "VideoObject",
    "name": {{ article.title | json }},
    "description": {{ vdesc | json }},
    "thumbnailUrl": [
      "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/{{ yt }}/hqdefault.jpg",
      "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/{{ yt }}/maxresdefault.jpg"
    ],
    "uploadDate": {{ article.metafields.custom.video_upload_date | json }},
    {%- if article.metafields.custom.video_duration != blank %}
    "duration": {{ article.metafields.custom.video_duration | json }},
    {%- endif %}
    "embedUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/{{ yt }}",
    "contentUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={{ yt }}",
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "ASR Outdoor",
      "url": "https://asroutdoor.com"
    }
  }
  </script>
{%- endif -%}
